1.title: When Fantasy Meets Reality
1.plot: Gonzo, Nick and Parv make their way to Seattle where they go on street patrol with Phoenix Jones and his rag-tag crew of real life crime fighters, known as the Rain City Superheroes, to learn the motivations behind the masked vigilantes much ridiculed actions.

2.title: Family Matters
2.plot: Nick, Gonzo and Parv head to southern Illinois to attend the lawless 'Gathering of The Juggalos' music festival, notorious with fans of horror-core hip-hop group Insane Clown Posse.

3.title: Inhibition and Exhibition
3.plot: With Kanye West's former manager John Monopoly as their guide, Nick, Gonzo and Parv find themselves on the dangerous streets of south-side Chicago. In Chicago, they discover that music is the only way to escape the ghettos for many of the young rappers who are the face of the burgeoning rap scene.

4.title: The Boyz in the Hood
4.plot: The boys are thrown in to the deep-end of the L.A. porn scene as they are invited on to the set of Austin Powers XXX for three days, where beautiful women and well-hung men disrobe in the hyper- real adult movie world.

5.title: Waking Up from the American Dream
5.plot: In Detroit, Gonzo, Parv and Nick find a city that appears to be on the brink of extinction, but are soon inspired by the proud locals who are rejuvenating the city, using the abandoned buildings and many vacant lots to create a new type of urban community where innovation and collaboration is key.

6.title: On the Road
6.plot: Take it as a final glimpse of the Unplanned madness that can happen when you throw away your Lonely Planet guide.

1.title: The Ties That Bind
1.plot: In the season premiere, the guys light up and join an official '420' bus tour of Denver exploring the recent legalization of marijuana in Colorado.

2.title: Rocky Mountain High
2.plot: Welcome to the wonderful world of sexual submission and domination, which goes way beyond 50 Shades of Grey as our trio kick off the trip with a very 'interactive' visit to a BDSM Training Chateau in Upstate New York, and quickly find out there are certain things that you just can't unseen.

3.title: Food for Thought
3.plot: From getting a warped lesson in America's obesity epidemic by tackling 20,000 calorie burgers at the Heart Attack Grill in Las Vegas to spending Christmas lunch at Albuquerque's biggest homeless shelter, the Unplanned America guys get some food for thought.

4.title: Marked Men
4.plot: Nick, Parv and Gonzo explore tattoo culture in Southern California, first getting tattoos at the legendary Shamrock Social Club before witnessing gang members have their lives turned around through tattoo removal before finally spending time with cancer victim Dawn who is undergoing aureole tattooing as part of restorative breast surgery.

5.title: Naked Truth
5.plot: The Unplanned America guys head to Portland, Oregon, the unlikely strip club capital of the USA, to get the lowdown on what it's like to work in this stigmatized industry spending time with club owners, dancers and those who work to help women that may be exploited by the industry.

6.title: Born on the Bayou
6.plot: Parv, Gonzo and Nick head to New Orleans and get swept up by the musical soul of the city from joyous second line bands, busking crust punks and twerking clubs, to throwing their very own street parade.

1.title: Blood, Sweat and Beers
1.plot: The ultra competitive World Beer Pong Championships in Las Vegas to life on the fringes of society at an anarchist skateboarding commune in Ohio, the boys explore some uniquely American sporting culture.

2.title: Life Off the Grid
2.plot: From spending time with the Lumbee Indians of North Carolina to exploring Voodoo culture in New Orleans, the Unplanned America guys get a first hand look at the clash between cultures of the old world and new.

3.title: Sex and Sellability
3.plot: The boys get an insight into what goes down on the other side of the computer screen when they visit three women who make their living as 'cam girls' providing adult entertainment over the internet. Later, they head to New York City for their fetish latex fitting with The Baroness.

4.title: Clash of Cultures
4.plot: The guys get to know the residents of the 'world's biggest open-air mental asylum' in New Mexico's Taos Mesa before meeting Carlos - a man determined to live off the grid on the fringes of Albuquerque despite the almost daily threat of dangerous drug cartels.

5.title: The Shaman on the Mount
5.plot: Aussie mates Gonzo, Nick and Parv continue to travel the USA, exploring the lesser seen side of American culture.The guys get in touch with their spiritual side, visiting a cannabis shaman in the Colorado mountains where they each face their darkest demons and also fear for their lives.

6.title: Guns 'n' Ammo
6.plot: In the season finale, Aussie mates Gonzo, Nick and Parv explore gun culture in America, spending time with the Virginia Open Carry Organisation, the Texas Militia and the friendly folk at Drive-A-Tank Wisconsin, people for whom the right to bear arms is at the very core of their beliefs.

imdb.title: Unplanned America
plot: _Unplanned America_ (qv) is the show about three Australians who throw away the itinerary and find themselves in the most weird, wonderful, intimidating and inspiring societies that the land of the free has to offer.::Tim Gonzo Ryan
